snippet.textDisplay: The scoville is not at all fake (we test for it in lab using a Gas Chromatograph-Mass Spectrophotometer), but it doesn't easily line up with perceived taste. The perceived spiciness of a food is more like the log of the scoville scale, meaning 1000 vs 2000 scovilles is a much bigger difference than 100,000 vs 200,000 scovilles.
snippet.textOriginal: The scoville is not at all fake (we test for it in lab using a Gas Chromatograph-Mass Spectrophotometer), but it doesn't easily line up with perceived taste.
